pr_body:
* Changed classifiers in setup.py
* Changed Python and Django version notes in README;
* Added myself to CONTRIBUTORS.

We had our concurrent jobs set to 1 on Travis: d'oh!

<img width="661" alt="screen shot 2015-09-17 at 9 24 54 pm" src="https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2096628/9950671/937a51fc-5d82-11e5-9da3-b66f33a7efec.png">

@scikit-image/core

CLAModel now uses `isinstance(encoder, DeltaEncoder)` to special case the delta encoder.

@subutai please review

fixes #1829

This fixes the Kinto load tests with current master.

Since discovering issues through Kinto is unacceptable, I opened #512.

@Natim r?

Old Style:

```python
	    "TargetGroupHealth": [
	        [
	            {
	                "HealthCheckPort": "7001",
	                "Target": {
	                    "Id": "i-xxxxxxxx",
	                    "Port": 7001
	                },
	                "TargetHealth": {
	                    "State": "healthy"
	                }
	            }
	        ]
    ],
```

New Style:

```python
"TargetGroupHealth": [
        {
            "HealthCheckPort": "7001",
            "Target": {
                "Id": "i-xxxxxxxx",
                "Port": 7001
            },
            "TargetHealth": {
                "State": "healthy"
            }
        },
```

This will allow the security_monkey watcher to have a new ephemeral section for `TargetGroupHealth:*:Target:Id`

```
# search services management commands
az search service list -g {..rg}
az search service show -g {..rg} --name {...name}
az search service delete -g {..rg} --name {...name}
az search service delete -g {..rg} --name {...name} -y
az search service create -g {..rg} -n {...name} --sku {...sku}
az search service create -g {..rg} -n {...name} --sku {...sku} --replica-count {...replica} --partition-count {...partition} --location {...location}
az search service update -g {..rg} --name {...name} --replica-count {...replica} --partition-count {...partition}

# admin keys management commands
az search admin-key show -g {..rg} --service-name {...name}
az search admin-key renew -g {..rg} --service-name {...name} --key-kind primary
az search admin-key renew -g {..rg} --service-name {...name} --key-kind secondary

# query keys management commands
az search query-key list -g {..rg} --service-name {...name}
az search query-key create -g {..rg} --service-name {...name} --name {...keyname}
az search query-key delete -g {..rg} --service-name {...name} --key-value {...keyvalue}
```
